-- Roger Federer Beats Novak Djokovic to Regain Swiss Indoors Tennis Title
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-11-07T17:02:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-07/roger-federer-beats-novak-djokovic-to-regain-swiss-indoors-tennis-title.html
Roger Federer  beat Serbia’s  Novak Djokovic  in three sets to claim the Swiss Indoors tennis title
in Basel for a fourth time in five years.  The 29-year-old Swiss won 6-4, 3-6, 6-1 against Djokovic,
who ended his opponent’s winning run at the event last year. It
was Federer’s 65th title on the ATP Tour and fourth this year.  Elsewhere, Spain’s  David Ferrer  beat countryman Marcel
Granollers 7-5, 6-3 in the Valencia Open final.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  